# reCAPTCHA v3 site key (public, not secret) lives in contact.html's
# data-recaptcha-site-key attribute — that is the ONLY place it's set, for
# every environment (local dev, staging, production). There is no env var
# for it anymore; a prior VITE_RECAPTCHA_SITE_KEY GitHub Actions secret used
# to override it silently and drifted out of sync with contact.html, which
# is what broke the contact form. See LAUNCH-CHECKLIST.md's reCAPTCHA
# section for the two remaining sync points (site key in contact.html,
# secret key in server config.local.php).

# Server-side secret goes in public/api/config.local.php on Hostinger (not in git).